 get exposed to an unending converyer belt of mediocre acts, all who seem to be getting a lot more laughs that you. Subconsiouly you start to pick up their traits and quirks, their joke styles - even their dress sense\n\nUnfortunately, I didn\'t have the self-confidence to stick to my guns and just carry on doing what I\'d been doing (many of the more original acts complain of 10 years or more of shitty gigs before being any good) so instead, I changed my act - making it more generic and punchy.\n\nSoon I was\n\n--','Why the Berlin comedy scene is awesome','','draft','open','open','','','','','2012-09-29 17:27:44','2012-09-29 15:27:44','',0,'http://comedyinenglish.de/?p=384723',0,'post','',0),(384740,1,'2012-09-13 13:28:04','2012-09-13 11:28:04','Hello.\n\nI was a comedian in the UK (London) for 2 solid years before I\'d finally had too much. I wasn\'t too bad at it, but what got me down in the end is that I didn\'t recognise myself on stage any more. I\'d become a TV-friendly, quirky bag-o-fun with a bullet-proof 10 minutes, and I hated every minute of it.\n\nIt wasn\'t always like that for The Cliff. When I started I was full of enthusiasm and original ideas - I soon got a reputation as being original & funny so I got larger shows. That\'s when it all went wrong. In the larger paid gigs you get more, well, boring audiences','Why I much prefer being a comic in Berlin','','inherit','open','open','','384723-revision','','','2012-09-13 13:28:04','2012-09-13 11:28:04','',384723,'http://comedyinenglish.de/2012/09/13/384723-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(394614,1,'2012-09-18 01:47:38','2012-09-17 23:47:38','Hi I thought I would just share this list of English language open-mics in Berlin:\r\n\r\n<strong>Tuesday</strong>\r\n20:30 We are not Gemüsed @ <a href=\"http://sameheads.com/\">Sameheads</a>, Neukölln - <a href=\"http://maps.google.co.uk/maps?q=Sameheads,+Richardstra%C3%9Fe,+Berlin,+Germany&amp;hl=en&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;sll=52.509197,13.388429&amp;sspn=0.051822,0.169086