\'ll explore the \"right\" ways of communicating on stage... and in life? \n\nInstructor: Noah Telson\n\nRSVP by sending an email to:\nWORKSHOPS[at]COMEDYSPORTZ[dot]DE\n\nSpots are limited!\n\nWorkshops are 12€ for a single class or 30€ for 3 classes.\n\nDrop in and stretch your improv muscles. Experienced and non-experienced improvisors welcome! \n\nALL classes are taught in English<!-- owner: 177122732313880 venue: 61931423382 -->','Open Improv Class (Weekly Workout)','','publish','open','open','','open-improv-class-weekly-workout','','','2012-10-02 10:53:31','2012-10-02 08:53:31','',0,'http://comedyinenglish.de/ai1ec_event/open-improv-class-weekly-workout/?instance_id=',0,'ai1ec_event','',0),(644257,1,'2012-10-02 10:53:31','2012-10-02 08:53:31','<a href=\'https://www.facebook.com/events/272923806151774\' class=\'uibutton confirm\'>Event on Facebook</a><br><br><img src=\"http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/203501_272923806151774_336259886_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"img\" />Fish &amp; Whips is back in Berlin and we\'re TASTIER than ever! \n\nFeaturing:\n\n  * XARAH VON DEN VIELENREGEN - Burlesuqe \n\n  * DUO SONAMBUL - Mind reading \n\n  * VIKTORIA LAPIDUS  - Hula Hoop artist\n\n  * JESSICA GADANI - Singer\n\n  * GREGOR GRACIANO - Pianist \n\n\nHosted by JACK WOODHEAD (UK) - Pianist, Singer, &amp; Conferencier.\n\n\nFish &amp; Whips is now only ONCE a month so grab something sparkling (a drink will suffice) and we\'ll see you on 18th!  \n\nEntry: €8 / €10\n\nYou can \'like\' us at:\n<a rel=\"nowfollow\" href=\"http://www.facebook.com/pages/Fish-Whips-Cabaret/173648182714424?ref=ts\">facebook.com/pages/Fish-Whips-Cabaret/&hellip;</a><!-- owner: 530080551 venue: 61931423382 -->','Fish &amp; Whips Cabaret - September!','','publish','open','open','','fish-whips-cabaret-september','','','2012-10-02 10:53:31','2012-10-02 08:53:31','',0,'http://comedyinenglish.de/ai1ec_event/fish-whips-cabaret-september/?instance_id=',0,'ai1ec_event','',0),(644258,1,'2012-10-02 10:53:31','2012-10-02 08:53:31','<a href=\'https://www.facebook.com/events/470894802934541\' class=\'uibutton confirm\'>Event on Facebook</a><br><br><img src=\"http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-ash4/373511_470894802934541_1933172673_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"img\" />Not only is our favorite intellectual comic threatening to leave Berlin, he\'s also turning 30. Do I smell smoke? Time for a roast. \n\nThe Samstagbraten of James Harris, hosted by the Meisterbräter, Drew Portnoy. \n\nDownstairs at the Kook in the Laughskeller aka the Saferoom aka The Austrian Basement. \n\nRoasters:\n\nPassun\nSummer Banks\nPaul Salamone\nTim Whelan\nSean Hunter Williams\nKatie Maranda\nPerry \nDharmander Singh\nKati Thiemer\nGeorg Kammerer\nKevin McCallum\nStephen Hannah\n\n€4 with the password (ask James or Drew).\n\nAnd with the exceptional participation of Neil Numb.<!-- owner: 100000796543677 venue: 61931423382 -->','Samstagsbraten: James Harris','','publish','open','open','','samstagsbraten-james-harris','','','2012-10-02 10:53:31','2012-10-02 08:53:31','',0,'http://comedyinenglish.de/ai1ec_event/samstagsbraten-james-harris/?instance_id=',0,'ai1ec_event','',0),(644259,1,'2012-10-02 10:53:31','2012-10-02 08:53:31','<a href=\'https://www.facebook.com/events/265251220259746\' class=\'uibutton confirm\'>Event on Facebook</a><br><br><img src=\"http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc7/373200_265251220259746_404297089_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"img\" />After explosive beginnings, we are now onto Episode Four of The Fish Bowl...\n\nLive Music, English-Language Comedy and a DJ Afterparty, is the short version, but a more elaborate story might tell of what is now  well respected, fort-nightly event, supported the some of the very best talent around the live music and comedy scene in Berlin.\n\nThe first 3 shows averaged around 120 in attendance and saw our mini-grand piano being put to good use by musicians from France, Germany and the United States; roaring laughter at our comedians from Germany, Scotland, England, Wales and America; a very special, live, electronic performance from Wermonster(recently signed, Berlin based producer); not to mention, a live video link-up from our favourite Berlin comedians, at the Edinburgh Festival, before they returned and brought the house down with their crafted festival sets.\n\nThe venue itself is a large, multi-room space and the staff must certainly be some of the most helpful and friendly, in Berlin.\n\nTHIS WEEK: music will be shared by the sensational Rob Longstaff(acoustic), Tim Whelan(piano), Bruce Millar(Piano) and Mike Richards(acoustic duo). Comedy will be provided in the form of Katie Maranda(U.S), James Harris(U.K), Barry MacEoin(IRE) and Tamika Campbell(U.S.), . The after party will be taken care of by DJ Schaefchen.\n\nALSO.... It\'s only Neil “comedy host” Numb\'s birthday! So, we\'ll be cranking the party up a notch and giving him a good roasting from an old friend via our live video link-up. Excellent!\n\nYou really shouldn\'t miss this one.\n\nSee you there,\n\nChris &amp; Neil\nThe Fish Bowl Team\n\nMore info can be found on the fish bowl page here: <a rel=\"nowfollow\" href=\"www.facebook.com/thefishbowlberlin\">facebook.com/&hellip;</a>\nDoors open at 8pm show starts at 9.30pm\nVenue - Naherholung Sternchen\nBerolinastraße 7\n10178 Berlin / Mitte\n<!-- owner: 459031607455471 venue: 459031607455471 -->','The Fish Bowl -  Episode Four','','publish','open','open','','the-fish-bowl-episode-four','','','2012-10-02 10:53:31','2012-10-02 08:53:31','',0,'http://comedyinenglish.de/ai1ec_event/the-fish-bowl-episode-four/?instance_id=',0,'ai1ec_event','',0),(644260,1,'2012-10-02 10:53:31','2012-10-02 08:53:31','<a href=\'https://www.facebook.com/events/462852000401916\' class=\'uibutton confirm\'>Event on Facebook</a><br><br><img src=\"http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-ash4/187904_462852000401916_1224266874_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"img\" />Summer break is over!  We\'re back at the Comedyclub Kookaburra for our regular Tuesday night prime time improvised comedy show! Full length, bare-knuckled brawls, on stage, for your laughs (in English).\n\nTickets at the door. 10/8€\n\nDoors open at 8:00pm \nSHOW STARTS AT 8:30 (this ain\'t no basement jam, things start on time!)<!-- owner: 177122732313880 venue: 61931423382 -->','ComedySportz! Prime time show at the Kook! (we\'re back!)','','publish','open','open','','comedysportz-prime-time-show-at-the-kook-were-back','','','2012-10-02 10:53:31','2012-10-02 08:53:31','',0,'http://comedyinenglish.de/ai1ec_event/comedysportz-prime-time-show-at-the-kook-were-back/?instance_id=',0,'ai1ec_event','',0),(644261,1,'2012-10-02 10:53:31','2012-10-02 08:53:31','<a href=\'https://www.facebook.com/events/260236260754514\' class=\'uibutton confirm\'>Event on Facebook</a><br><br><img src=\"http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/276813_260236260754514_42558814_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"img\" />I did it once this spring but I\'ve got more jokes, more confidence and two more kilos. So let\'s do it again: \n\nDrugs. Sex. Alcohol. And babies. \n\nWe\'ll start midnight-ish. €8 at the door. \n\nDownstairs in the Laughskeller aka the Saferoom at the Kook (unelss we get tons of reservations and then it\'ll be upstairs). <!-- owner: 100000796543677 venue: 61931423382 -->','The Enemy\'s in the Kinderzimmer','','publish','open','open','','the-enemys-in-the-kinderzimmer','','','2012-10-02 10:53:31','2012-10-02 08:53:31','',0,'http://comedyinenglish.de/ai1ec_event/the-enemys-in-the-kinderzimmer/?instance_id=',0,'ai1ec_event','',0),(644262,1,'2012-10-02 10:53:31','2012-10-02 08:53:31','<a href=\'https://www.facebook.com/events/450056565039468\' class=\'uibutton confirm\'>Event on Facebook</a><br><br><img src=\"http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-snc6/188171_450056565039468_1206612573_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"img\" />English Comedy Night is back!   And we are starting off with a bang!  TV regular, full of class and full of pazzaz,  Knacki Deuser ( Mr  „Nightwash“),  brilliant madcap music with The Beez,  the explosive  Sanjay Shihora  (the man who taught Karma Sutra to the grizzly bears), surprises! and your host Kim Eustice ( back Up Here form Down Under) <!-- owner: 707553234 venue: 61931423382 -->','The English Comedy Night','','publish','open','open','','the-english-comedy-night','','','2012-10-02 10:53:31','2012-10-02 08:53:31','',0,'http://comedyinenglish.de/ai1ec_event/the-english-comedy-night/?instance_id=',0,'ai1ec_event','',0),(644263,1,'2012-10-02 10:53:31','2012-10-02 08:53:31','<a href=\'https://www.facebook.com/events/509259635757097\' class=\'uibutton confirm\'>Event on Facebook</a><br><br><img src=\"http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-ash4/195755_509259635757097_837867170_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"img\" />Now on it\'s third outing, The Fish Bowl entered on and epic wave and is here to stay, thanks to the support of some very talented performers and fantastic audiences.\n\nEpisodes One &amp; Two proved that when you mix accomplished live musicians, Berlin\'s best English-speaking comedians,  danceable tunes and some friendly people- in a Bowl- beauty, madness and serious moves are the inevitable result.\n\nPresented by Chris Glen and Neil Numb, The Fish Bowl is held every fortnight and plays host to:\n\nLive Music \nEnglish-Language Comedy\nand a DJ Afterparty\n\nTHIS WEEK sees the returns of some of Berlin\'s finest and funniest, fresh from their residency at the world renowned Edinburgh Festival, as well as, live performances by Lewis Maxwell, Chris Glen &amp;  special guest. The after party will be taken care of in the form electronic collaboration from DJ\'s/Producers Kurtz and Nick Dow.\n\n\nMore info can be found on the fish bowl page here: <a rel=\"nowfollow\" href=\"www.facebook.com/thefishbowlberlin\">facebook.com/&hellip;</a>\n\nSee you there,\n\nThe Fish Bowl Team<!-- owner: 459031607455471 venue: 459031607455471 -->','The Fish Bowl -  Episode Three','','publish','open','open','','the-fish-bowl-episode-three','','','2012-10-02 10:53:31','2012-10-02 08:53:31','',0,'http://comedyinenglish.de/ai1ec_event/the-fish-bowl-episode-three/?instance_id=',0,'ai1ec_event','',0),(644264,1,'2012-10-02 10:53:31','2012-10-02 08:53:31','<a href=\'https://www.facebook.com/events/452182831478825\' class=\'uibutton confirm\'>Event on Facebook</a><br><br><img src=\"http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/hprofile-ak-ash4/187961_452182831478825_1146573118_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"img\" />After an explosive launch on the 2nd Aug we are now straight back into preparations for Episode Two! Line-up is being announced on The Fish Bowl Page <a rel=\"nowfollow\" href=\"www.facebook.com/thefishbowlberlin\">facebook.com/&hellip;</a> over the next week.\n\n**\n\nFellow Scots, musician and Buzz Club co-founder, Chris Glen and comedian, Neil Numb present the second instalment of a brand new collaboration of art, live music, English comedy and DJ\'s.\n\nThe Fish Bowl.\n\nHeld every fortnight, the events play host to:\n\n\n Exhibiting Artists\n Live Music Acts\n Comedians\n DJ\'s\n RC Flying Fish\n\nInfo about the artists can be found on the fish bowl page here: <a rel=\"nowfollow\" href=\"www.facebook.com/thefishbowlberlin\">facebook.com/&hellip;</a>\n\n\n**Both heavily involved in the emerging art,comedy and small stage events, thriving in pockets all over Berlin, Neil and Chris have joined forces to bring the very best of what\'s going on walls and stages across the city, together, under one glorious umbrella. Combining an open and friendly attitude to supporting the creative arts and a commitment to sponsoring a thriving and supportive community of artists, creators and appreciators, we hope that with the help of some friends and supporters, we can contribute a well orchestrated, symphony of inspiration, sight and sound for your enjoyment and wonder. **\n\n\nWe look forward to introducing you to some wonderful people whom we have found.\n\nBest regards,\n\nThe Fish Bowl<!--